52.5	Arthur_C_Clarke	Arthur C. Clarke	Sir Arthur Charles Clarke, CBE, FRAS, Sri Lankabhimanya, (16 December 1917 â€“ 19 March 2008) was a British science fiction author, inventor, and futurist, famous for his short stories and novels, among them 2001: A Space Odyssey (1968), and as a host and commentator in the British television series Mysterious World. For many years, Robert A. Heinlein, Isaac Asimov, and Clarke were known as the "Big Three" of science fiction.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Clarke_sm.jpg/220px-Clarke_sm.jpg
